            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Also for testing in nvim-treesitter repo you can use the expanded commands as shown below, as you can see the output for left and right is the same.\r\n\r\n$ git log --pretty=format:%m\\ %h\\ \\|\\ %s%d --decorate-refs=refst/tags --topo-order --left-only 6620ae1c...7caec274\r\n\\> 7caec274 | bot(parsers): update beancount, gotmpl, heex, helm, idl, javadoc, jinja, jinja_inline, just, kotlin, liquid, mlir, ocaml, ocaml_interface, pkl, pod, rust, supercollider, typoscript\r\n\\> da8bf82a | fix(kotlin): regex and printf injections not applying (#8613)\r\n\\> f059649b | fix(go): highlight rune as `@character` (#8612)\r\n\r\n$ git log --pretty=format:%m\\ %h\\ \\|\\ %s%d --decorate-refs=refst/tags --topo-order --right-only 6620ae1c...7caec274\r\n\\> 7caec274 | bot(parsers): update beancount, gotmpl, heex, helm, idl, javadoc, jinja, jinja_inline, just, kotlin, liquid, mlir, ocaml, ocaml_interface, pkl, pod, rust, supercollider, typoscript\r\n\\> da8bf82a | fix(kotlin): regex and printf injections not applying (#8613)\r\n\\> f059649b | fix(go): highlight rune as `@character` (#8612)",
