        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks for the PR!\r\n\r\n> Also for testing in nvim-treesitter repo you can use the expanded commands as shown below, as you can see the output for left and right is the same.\r\n\r\nSimilar as described [in this comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38526#issuecomment-4147962721), I can not reproduce this. The `--left-only` returns nothing while `--right-only` returns three commits.\r\n\r\nIf anything, this looks like an issue in the Git version itself. And chances are, it is already resolved and updating Git version should fix this.\r\n\r\nI also remember looking into the `--left-right` and there were some problems. Not *quite* remember which ones, but probably not consistent order of `>` and `<` commits or the fact that it can't force (what looks to me like) their preferred order (first \"left\", then \"right\").",
